<body>
  <h1>TryHackMe — Beginner Roadmap (HTML)</h1>

  <p class="note">
    Use this roadmap only for legal, ethical learning. Practice in isolated labs and VMs you own or have explicit permission to test.
  </p>

  <section class="card">
    <h2>Recommended learning paths (order)</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <strong>Complete Beginner</strong> — Start here if you're new to cybersecurity.
        <div class="meta"><a href="https://tryhackme.com/path/complete-beginner" target="_blank">TryHackMe: Complete Beginner</a> • Est. time: 6–10 hrs • Difficulty: Very Low</div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Pre-Security</strong> — Foundations: networking, Linux, Windows basics.
        <div class="meta"><a href="https://tryhackme.com/path/pre-security" target="_blank">TryHackMe: Pre-Security</a> • Est. time: 8–12 hrs • Difficulty: Low</div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Web Fundamentals</strong> — Web concepts and OWASP basics (safe, defensive learning).
        <div class="meta"><a href="https://tryhackme.com/path/web-fundamentals" target="_blank">TryHackMe: Web Fundamentals</a> • Est. time: 6–10 hrs • Difficulty: Low–Medium</div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Junior Penetration Tester (optional)</strong> — Practical staged labs and realistic boxes.
        <div class="meta"><a href="https://tryhackme.com/path/junior-penetration-tester" target="_blank">TryHackMe: Junior Penetration Tester</a> • Est. time: 20–40 hrs • Difficulty: Medium</div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Blue Team / Defensive Paths</strong> — If you want to focus on defense, sysadmin, detection.
        <div class="meta"><a href="https://tryhackme.com/path/blue-team" target="_blank">TryHackMe: Blue Team</a> • Est. time: varies • Difficulty: Low–High</div>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="card">
    <h2>High-value beginner rooms (suggested sequence)</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Intro to Cyber Security / Intro to Offensive Security</strong> — orientation and safe ethics.</li>
      <li><strong>Linux Fundamentals</strong> — terminal, files, users, permissions.</li>
      <li><strong>Windows Fundamentals</strong> — Windows basics, PowerShell intro, services.</li>
      <li><strong>Nmap</strong> — network discovery and port scanning (use on your lab only).</li>
      <li><strong>HTTP Basics / Web Fundamentals</strong> — request/response, forms, cookies.</li>
      <li><strong>OWASP Top 10 Overview</strong> — high-level web vulnerabilities and defenses.</li>
      <li><strong>Basic Forensics / Logging</strong> — defensive skills: log analysis and incident response.</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="meta">Search these room titles on TryHackMe or follow the path links above. Estimated time per room: 30–90 mins depending on depth.</div>
  </section>

  <section class="card">
    <h2>Practical setup & safety tips</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Run Kali and target VMs inside VirtualBox/VMware on an isolated "host-only" or "internal" network.</li>
      <li>Take snapshots before experimenting so you can revert quickly.</li>
      <li>Never attack machines you don't own or don't have explicit written permission to test.</li>
      <li>Use TryHackMe's browser-based lab (if available) to avoid local setup for some rooms.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="card">
    <h2>Next recommended steps</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Create a TryHackMe account (if you don't have one) and complete the "Complete Beginner" path.</li>
      <li>Set up two VMs (Kali + Windows 11 or a vulnerable target) on an isolated network and practice Nmap and basics.</li>
      <li>Pick one focused goal: web security, Linux admin, or incident response — follow the matching TryHackMe path.</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <p class="note">If you want, I can generate a downloadable checklist (PDF/HTML) with step-by-step instructions to set up the lab safely. Which format do you prefer?</p>
